25class ProgramPrelude : public TIntermTraverser
26{
27 using LineTag = unsigned;
28 using FuncEmitter = void (*)(ProgramPrelude &, const TFunction &);
29 using FuncToEmitter = std::map<Name, FuncEmitter>;
30
31 public:
32 ProgramPrelude(TInfoSinkBase &out, const ProgramPreludeConfig &ppc)
33 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, false), mOut(out)
34 {
35 ALWAYS_INLINE();
36 int_clamp();
37 if (ppc.hasStructEq)
38 {
39 equalVector();
40 equalMatrix();
41 }
42
43 switch (ppc.shaderType)
44 {
45 case MetalShaderType::None:
46 ASSERT(0 && "ppc.shaderType should not be ShaderTypeNone");
47 break;
48 case MetalShaderType::Vertex:
49 transform_feedback_guard();
50 break;
51 case MetalShaderType::Fragment:
52 writeSampleMask();
53 break;
54 case MetalShaderType::Compute:
55 ASSERT(0 && "compute shaders not currently supported");
56 break;
57 default:
58 break;
59 }
60
61#if 1
62 mOut << "#define ANGLE_tensor metal::array\n";
63 mOut << "#pragma clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-value\"\n";
64#else
65 tensor();
66#endif
67 }
68
69 private:
70 bool emitGuard(LineTag lineTag)
71 {
72 if (mEmitted.find(lineTag) != mEmitted.end())
73 {
74 return false;
75 }
76 mEmitted.insert(lineTag);
77 return true;
78 }
79
80 static FuncToEmitter BuildFuncToEmitter();
81
82 void visitOperator(TOperator op,
83 const TFunction *func,
84 const TType *argType0,
85 const TType *argType1 = nullptr,
86 const TType *argType2 = nullptr);
87 void visitVariable(const Name &name, const TType &type);
88 void visitVariable(const TVariable &var);
89 void visitStructure(const TStructure &s);
90
91 bool visitBinary(Visit, TIntermBinary *node) override;
92 bool visitUnary(Visit, TIntermUnary *node) override;
93 bool visitAggregate(Visit, TIntermAggregate *node) override;
94 bool visitDeclaration(Visit, TIntermDeclaration *node) override;
95 void visitSymbol(TIntermSymbol *node) override;
96

263#define PROGRAM_PRELUDE_INCLUDE(header) \
264 void ProgramPrelude::include_##header() \
265 { \
266 if (emitGuard(__LINE__)) \
267 { \
268 mOut << ("#include <" #header ">\n\n"); \
269 } \
270 }
271
272#define PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(name, code, ...) \
273 void ProgramPrelude::name() \
274 { \
275 ASSERT(code[0] == '\n'); \
276 if (emitGuard(__LINE__)) \
277 { \
278 __VA_ARGS__; /* dependencies */ \
279 mOut << (static_cast<const char *>(code "\n") + 1); \
280 } \
281 }

601PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(refract,
602 R"(
603template <typename T, typename Enable = void>
604struct ANGLE_refract_impl
605{
606 static ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE T exec(T i, T n, ANGLE_scalar_of_t<T> eta)
607 {
608 return metal::refract(i, n, eta);
609 }
610};
611template <typename T>
612struct ANGLE_refract_impl<T, ANGLE_enable_if_t<ANGLE_is_scalar<T>::value>>
613{
614 static ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE T exec(T i, T n, T eta)
615 {
616 auto dotNI = n * i;
617 auto k = T(1) - eta * eta * (T(1) - dotNI * dotNI);
618 if (k < T(0))
619 {
620 return T(0);
621 }
622 else
623 {
624 return eta * i - (eta * dotNI + metal::sqrt(k)) * n;
625 }
626 }
627};
628template <typename T>
629ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE T ANGLE_refract(T i, T n, ANGLE_scalar_of_t<T> eta)
630{
631 return ANGLE_refract_impl<T>::exec(i, n, eta);
632};
633)",
634 include_metal_math(),
635 include_metal_geometric(),
636 enable_if(),
637 is_scalar(),
638 is_vector(),
639 is_matrix())

974PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(inverse2, R"(
975template <typename T>
976ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, 2, 2> ANGLE_inverse(metal::matrix<T, 2, 2> m)
977{
978 metal::matrix<T, 2, 2> adj;
979 adj[0][0] = m[1][1];
980 adj[0][1] = -m[0][1];
981 adj[1][0] = -m[1][0];
982 adj[1][1] = m[0][0];
983 T det = (adj[0][0] * m[0][0]) + (adj[0][1] * m[1][0]);
984 return adj * (T(1) / det);
985}
986)")

988PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(inverse3, R"(
989template <typename T>
990ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, 3, 3> ANGLE_inverse(metal::matrix<T, 3, 3> m)
991{
992 T a = m[1][1] * m[2][2] - m[2][1] * m[1][2];
993 T b = m[1][0] * m[2][2];
994 T c = m[1][2] * m[2][0];
995 T d = m[1][0] * m[2][1];
996 T det = m[0][0] * (a) -
997 m[0][1] * (b - c) +
998 m[0][2] * (d - m[1][1] * m[2][0]);
999 det = T(1) / det;
1000 metal::matrix<T, 3, 3> minv;
1001 minv[0][0] = (a) * det;
1002 minv[0][1] = (m[0][2] * m[2][1] - m[0][1] * m[2][2]) * det;
1003 minv[0][2] = (m[0][1] * m[1][2] - m[0][2] * m[1][1]) * det;
1004 minv[1][0] = (c - b) * det;
1005 minv[1][1] = (m[0][0] * m[2][2] - m[0][2] * m[2][0]) * det;
1006 minv[1][2] = (m[1][0] * m[0][2] - m[0][0] * m[1][2]) * det;
1007 minv[2][0] = (d - m[2][0] * m[1][1]) * det;
1008 minv[2][1] = (m[2][0] * m[0][1] - m[0][0] * m[2][1]) * det;
1009 minv[2][2] = (m[0][0] * m[1][1] - m[1][0] * m[0][1]) * det;
1010 return minv;
1011}
1012)")
1013
1014PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(inverse4, R"(
1015template <typename T>
1016ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, 4, 4> ANGLE_inverse(metal::matrix<T, 4, 4> m)
1017{
1018 T A2323 = m[2][2] * m[3][3] - m[2][3] * m[3][2];
1019 T A1323 = m[2][1] * m[3][3] - m[2][3] * m[3][1];
1020 T A1223 = m[2][1] * m[3][2] - m[2][2] * m[3][1];
1021 T A0323 = m[2][0] * m[3][3] - m[2][3] * m[3][0];
1022 T A0223 = m[2][0] * m[3][2] - m[2][2] * m[3][0];
1023 T A0123 = m[2][0] * m[3][1] - m[2][1] * m[3][0];
1024 T A2313 = m[1][2] * m[3][3] - m[1][3] * m[3][2];
1025 T A1313 = m[1][1] * m[3][3] - m[1][3] * m[3][1];
1026 T A1213 = m[1][1] * m[3][2] - m[1][2] * m[3][1];
1027 T A2312 = m[1][2] * m[2][3] - m[1][3] * m[2][2];
1028 T A1312 = m[1][1] * m[2][3] - m[1][3] * m[2][1];
1029 T A1212 = m[1][1] * m[2][2] - m[1][2] * m[2][1];
1030 T A0313 = m[1][0] * m[3][3] - m[1][3] * m[3][0];
1031 T A0213 = m[1][0] * m[3][2] - m[1][2] * m[3][0];
1032 T A0312 = m[1][0] * m[2][3] - m[1][3] * m[2][0];
1033 T A0212 = m[1][0] * m[2][2] - m[1][2] * m[2][0];
1034 T A0113 = m[1][0] * m[3][1] - m[1][1] * m[3][0];
1035 T A0112 = m[1][0] * m[2][1] - m[1][1] * m[2][0];
1036 T a = m[1][1] * A2323 - m[1][2] * A1323 + m[1][3] * A1223;
1037 T b = m[1][0] * A2323 - m[1][2] * A0323 + m[1][3] * A0223;
1038 T c = m[1][0] * A1323 - m[1][1] * A0323 + m[1][3] * A0123;
1039 T d = m[1][0] * A1223 - m[1][1] * A0223 + m[1][2] * A0123;
1040 T det = m[0][0] * ( a )
1041 - m[0][1] * ( b )
1042 + m[0][2] * ( c )
1043 - m[0][3] * ( d );
1044 det = T(1) / det;
1045 metal::matrix<T, 4, 4> im;
1046 im[0][0] = det * ( a );
1047 im[0][1] = det * - ( m[0][1] * A2323 - m[0][2] * A1323 + m[0][3] * A1223 );
1048 im[0][2] = det * ( m[0][1] * A2313 - m[0][2] * A1313 + m[0][3] * A1213 );
1049 im[0][3] = det * - ( m[0][1] * A2312 - m[0][2] * A1312 + m[0][3] * A1212 );
1050 im[1][0] = det * - ( b );
1051 im[1][1] = det * ( m[0][0] * A2323 - m[0][2] * A0323 + m[0][3] * A0223 );
1052 im[1][2] = det * - ( m[0][0] * A2313 - m[0][2] * A0313 + m[0][3] * A0213 );
1053 im[1][3] = det * ( m[0][0] * A2312 - m[0][2] * A0312 + m[0][3] * A0212 );
1054 im[2][0] = det * ( c );
1055 im[2][1] = det * - ( m[0][0] * A1323 - m[0][1] * A0323 + m[0][3] * A0123 );
1056 im[2][2] = det * ( m[0][0] * A1313 - m[0][1] * A0313 + m[0][3] * A0113 );
1057 im[2][3] = det * - ( m[0][0] * A1312 - m[0][1] * A0312 + m[0][3] * A0112 );
1058 im[3][0] = det * - ( d );
1059 im[3][1] = det * ( m[0][0] * A1223 - m[0][1] * A0223 + m[0][2] * A0123 );
1060 im[3][2] = det * - ( m[0][0] * A1213 - m[0][1] * A0213 + m[0][2] * A0113 );
1061 im[3][3] = det * ( m[0][0] * A1212 - m[0][1] * A0212 + m[0][2] * A0112 );
1062 return im;
1063}

1355PROGRAM_PRELUDE_DECLARE(castMatrix,
1356 R"(
1357template <typename T, int C1, int R1, int C2, int R2, typename Enable = void>
1358struct ANGLE_castMatrix
1359{
1360 static ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, C1, R1> exec(metal::matrix<T, C2, R2> const m2)
1361 {
1362 metal::matrix<T, C1, R1> m1;
1363 const int MinC = C1 <= C2 ? C1 : C2;
1364 const int MinR = R1 <= R2 ? R1 : R2;
1365 for (int c = 0; c < MinC; ++c)
1366 {
1367 for (int r = 0; r < MinR; ++r)
1368 {
1369 m1[c][r] = m2[c][r];
1370 }
1371 for (int r = R2; r < R1; ++r)
1372 {
1373 m1[c][r] = c == r ? T(1) : T(0);
1374 }
1375 }
1376 for (int c = C2; c < C1; ++c)
1377 {
1378 for (int r = 0; r < R1; ++r)
1379 {
1380 m1[c][r] = c == r ? T(1) : T(0);
1381 }
1382 }
1383 return m1;
1384 }
1385};
1386template <typename T, int C1, int R1, int C2, int R2>
1387struct ANGLE_castMatrix<T, C1, R1, C2, R2, ANGLE_enable_if_t<(C1 <= C2 && R1 <= R2)>>
1388{
1389 static ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, C1, R1> exec(metal::matrix<T, C2, R2> const m2)
1390 {
1391 metal::matrix<T, C1, R1> m1;
1392 for (size_t c = 0; c < C1; ++c)
1393 {
1394 m1[c] = ANGLE_cast<R1>(m2[c]);
1395 }
1396 return m1;
1397 }
1398};
1399template <int C1, int R1, int C2, int R2, typename T>
1400ANGLE_ALWAYS_INLINE metal::matrix<T, C1, R1> ANGLE_cast(metal::matrix<T, C2, R2> const m)
1401{
1402 return ANGLE_castMatrix<T, C1, R1, C2, R2>::exec(m);
1403};

3003////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3004
3005// Returned Name is valid for as long as `buffer` is still alive.
3006// Returns false if no template args exist.
3007// Returns false if buffer is not large enough.
3008//
3009// Example:
3010// "foo<1,2>" --> "foo<>"
3011static std::pair<Name, bool> MaskTemplateArgs(const Name &name, size_t bufferSize, char *buffer)
3012{
3013 const char *begin = name.rawName().data();
3014 const char *end = strchr(begin, '<');
3015 if (!end)
3016 {
3017 return {{}, false};
3018 }
3019 size_t n = end - begin;
3020 if (n + 3 > bufferSize)
3021 {
3022 return {{}, false};
3023 }
3024 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i)
3025 {
3026 buffer[i] = begin[i];
3027 }
3028 buffer[n + 0] = '<';
3029 buffer[n + 1] = '>';
3030 buffer[n + 2] = '\0';
3031 return {Name(buffer, name.symbolType()), true};
3032}

3821void ProgramPrelude::visitVariable(const Name &name, const TType &type)

3874
3875bool ProgramPrelude::visitAggregate(Visit visit, TIntermAggregate *node)
3876{
3877 const size_t argCount = node->getChildCount();
3878
3879 auto getArgType = [node, argCount](size_t index) -> const TType & {
3880 ASSERT(index < argCount);
3881 TIntermTyped *arg = node->getChildNode(index)->getAsTyped();
3882 ASSERT(arg);
3883 return arg->getType();
3884 };
3885
3886 const TFunction *func = node->getFunction();
3887
3888 switch (node->getChildCount())
3889 {
3890 case 0:
3891 {
3892 visitOperator(node->getOp(), func, nullptr);
3893 }
3894 break;
3895
3896 case 1:
3897 {
3898 const TType &argType0 = getArgType(0);
3899 visitOperator(node->getOp(), func, &argType0);
3900 }
3901 break;
3902
3903 case 2:
3904 {
3905 const TType &argType0 = getArgType(0);
3906 const TType &argType1 = getArgType(1);
3907 visitOperator(node->getOp(), func, &argType0, &argType1);
3908 }
3909 break;
3910
3911 case 3:
3912 {
3913 const TType &argType0 = getArgType(0);
3914 const TType &argType1 = getArgType(1);
3915 const TType &argType2 = getArgType(2);
3916 visitOperator(node->getOp(), func, &argType0, &argType1, &argType2);
3917 }
3918 break;
3919
3920 default:
3921 {
3922 const TType &argType0 = getArgType(0);
3923 const TType &argType1 = getArgType(1);
3924 visitOperator(node->getOp(), func, &argType0, &argType1);
3925 }
3926 break;
3927 }
3928
3929 return true;
3930}

3932bool ProgramPrelude::visitDeclaration(Visit, TIntermDeclaration *node)

3941 }
